publicationStmt.p: Transcription of the Bodleian Library "Register C" (Library Records c.854) with added provenance and title data. This document is part of a MA thesis at Humboldt Universität zu Berlin (MA Library and Information Science)

sourceDesc.p: Bodleian Library Record c.854, known as Register C, is an account book of the Bodleian Library for the years 1720-1767. It records, in various hands, expenses, books bought, donated and given to the library as well as the moving of books to other shelves.

encodingDesc.p: Shelfmarks are transcibed as they appear in the source. Additionally, a 'normalized' form corresponding to the form shelfmarks are used in today's catalogue (with spaces and stops at the appropriate positions) is provided in a 'choice'-element.

The tables in the source are reproduced as tables, but brackets indicating alignments of rows or dots filling the line are not reproduced (where appropriate, cells spanning multiple colums or rows are marked as such.

monogr.author: Willis, Browne, 1682-1760.
monogr.title: An history of the mitred Parliamentary abbies, and conventual cathedral churches. : Shewing the times of their respective foundations, and what alterations they have undergone. With some descriptions of their monuments, and dimensions of their buildings, &c. Together with a catalogue of their abbats, priors, &c. To which are annexed, several other lists of the principals of divers monasteries; the number of monks at the surrender, and the names of the last abbats, priors, &c. who signed the same; as far as they have come to hand. With an exact account of those religious men and women, and chantry priests, receiving pensions throughout England and Wales, An. 1553. A work, among other uses, necessary to give light to several charters sans date; and helpful to such who shall treat of families and dignified persons. For whose benefit are subjoined large indexes. The whole extracted out of very curious manuscripts, &c. which have been many years colecting by the most eminent antiquaries; and faithfully published. /

front.p:
Order'd by the Curators of the Bodleian Library
1. That the MSS. supra and Superius Seld now under
the Inspection of the Senr. Proctor be Professor
of Gr. be transfer'd to the Senior Proctor; and that
both of them have new Curating Books finish'd
before Nov.r next.
2. That all the MSS. which are out of repair in their
binding be repair'd or new bound.
That the Rest of the Books in the Library below
Stairs, be placed according to their sizes (as
near as may be) in the same manner with those
in Arts under the Inspection of the Senr. Proctor.

row.cell:
Order'd also that this Visitation
be adjourn'd 'till this day-
fortnight between Eight &
Nine in the morning.

Feb.14.174¾ At a general meeting of yͤ Delegates
of the Press, it was order'd, that every Author and Editor
who shall hereafter publish any Book from the University
Press shall deliver one copy of said Book Bound to the
chief Librarian of the Bodleian Library for the use
of the said Library before the Publication of the said
Book and that a Copy of this Order be given to
the said Chief Librarian.
